{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17595929","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17595929"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T11:08:30+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T11:08:30+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15381"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15381","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15381"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.17,0.52,0.17,0.13,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8072"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"63829"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8072","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8072"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15381"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"49259"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4928"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"8127"},{"type":"tags","id":"8761"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19592"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19593"},{"type":"contributions","id":"20858"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"63829","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/63829"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EIleus is a common post-operative complication affecting gastrointestinal function.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"With regards to post-operative ileus, which one of the following is most correct?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["It only affects the small intestine","It typically resolves within 2-3 days","Most cases are the result of mechanical bowel obstruction","Most cases require prompt surgical intervention","There is increased intestinal motility"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPost-operative ileus\u003C/strong\u003E is a temporary cessation of coordinated bowel motility that typically resolves within 2-3 days following surgery. This is considered the normal physiological response to abdominal surgery.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThere is decreased or absent rather than \u003Cstrong\u003Eincreased intestinal motility\u003C/strong\u003E in post-operative ileus. Ileus can affect both the small and large intestine. \u003Cstrong\u003ESurgical intervention\u003C/strong\u003E is not typically required for ileus, which is managed conservatively. \u003Cstrong\u003EMechanical bowel obstruction\u003C/strong\u003E is a different condition where there is a physical blockage of the intestine, unlike ileus which is a functional disorder of intestinal motility.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Ileus is a temporary cessation of coordinated bowel motility.","Post-operative ileus typically resolves within 2-3 days after surgery.","Ileus is characterised by decreased or absent intestinal motility, not increased motility."],"references":["Sommer NP, Schneider R, Wehner S, Kalff JC, Vilz TO. State-of-the-art colorectal disease: postoperative ileus. Int J Colorectal Dis. 2021 Sep;36(9):2017-2025. doi: 10.1007/s00384-021-03939-1. Epub 2021 May 11. PMID: 33977334; PMCID: PMC8346406.","Beach EC, De Jesus O. Ileus. 2023 Aug 23. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 32644363.","Yamada, T., Alpers, D. H., Kalloo, A. N., Kaplowitz, N., Owyang, C., \u0026 Powell, D. W. (Eds.). (2011). Textbook of gastroenterology. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision